  "texts": [
    "During the annotation process, it is possible to both add annotations to the original text or create a separate file for annotations.",
    "35 The former has the advantage of keeping both the text and annotations in a single file -such as an XML file -so the NLP algorithms have access to both.",
    "(b) Unsupervised: If unsupervised, learning requires no human input once the data is collected.",
    "There is no annotation stage.",
    "The project could involve multiple tasks that support each other by creating annotations, but as long as NLP relies only on pre-trained models and the final task does not involve humans, it would still be characterised as unsupervised training."
